### Fee Structure - Formulas & Tables

**Standard Trading Fee Formula:**
```
fees = round up(0.07 × C × P × (1-P))
```
Where:
- C = number of contracts
- P = price of contract in dollars (e.g., 50¢ = 0.5)
- Round up = rounds to nearest cent per contract

**Maker Fee Formula (some markets only):**
```
fees = round up(0.0175 × C × P × (1-P))
```
- 25% of standard taker fee
- Only charged when trade executes, not when canceled
- Check https://kalshi.com/fee-schedule for which markets have maker fees

**S&P500 and NASDAQ-100 Fee Formula:**
```
fees = round up(0.035 × C × P × (1-P))
```
- 50% of standard rate
- Applies to all markets with ticker beginning with INX or NASDAQ100

**Fee Table (100 contracts, standard rate):**
- $0.05: $0.34
- $0.10: $0.63
- $0.20: $1.12
- $0.30: $1.47
- $0.40: $1.68
